com.ezetap.sdk

Class EzetapApiConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ezetap.sdk.EzetapApiConfig

  • public class EzetapApiConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Ezetap API Config object. Use a populated instance of this class and call EzetapPayApis.create(EzetapApiConfig config) to initialize/override default parameters (set in com.ezetap.sdk.AppConstants)
    Author:
    vivek

    • Constructor Detail

      • EzetapApiConfig

        public EzetapApiConfig(com.ezetap.sdk.EzeConstants.LoginAuthMode authMode,
               java.lang.String appKey,
               java.lang.String merchantName,
               java.lang.String currencyCode,
               com.ezetap.sdk.EzeConstants.AppMode mode,
               boolean captureSignature,
               com.ezetap.sdk.EzeConstants.CommunicationChannel preferredChannel)
        Creates an instance of EzetapApiConfig with desired mode. Default/null will set mode to DEMO. Use this constructor to create an instance of EzetapApiConfig in case you want to override the default setting of captureSignature = false and set it to true. Setting it to true will enable the Ezetap signature capture UI to be shown during a payment transaction.
        Parameters:
        authMode - - Mode of Authentication as defined in enum LoginAuthMode
        EZETAP_LOGIN_PROMPT - User Authentication credentials input screen and validation handled by Ezetap
        EZETAP_LOGIN_CUSTOM - User Authentication credentials input screen handled by App and validation by Ezetap
        EZETAP_LOGIN_BYPASS - User Authentication is completely done by the App and notified to Ezetap (needs AppKey)
        By default, signature capture is disabled. To enable, call setCaptureSignature(true)
        appKey - - App Key (if applicable) provided by Ezetap for the merchant
        merchantName - - Name of the merchant
        currencyCode - - Currency code for the merchant (Defaulted to INR if null is passed)
        captureSignature - - flag defaulted to false. Set this to true if you require Ezetap to display the signature UI and capture signature as a Bitmap
        mode - - App mode as defined in enum AppMode
        EZETAP_DEMO - Application is in DEMO mode connecting to Ezetap's DEMO instance
        EZETAP_PROD - Application is in PROD mode connecting to Ezetap's PROD instance.
        Contact Ezetap prior to connecting to the PROD instance
        preferredChannel - - Specify which CommunicationChannel you wish set as default

        By default, signature capture is disabled. To enable, call setCaptureSignature(true)
        appKey - - App Key (if applicable) provided by Ezetap for the merchant
        merchantName - - Name of the merchant
        currencyCode - - Currency code for the merchant (Defaulted to INR if null is passed)
        captureSignature - - flag defaulted to false. Set this to true if you require Ezetap to display the signature UI and capture signature as a Bitmap
        mode - - App mode as defined in enum AppMode
